Privacy Policy
1. Data Collection
The bot collects and stores Discord user IDs and submitted BTC wallet addresses.
Audit logs are kept for administrative tracking.
2. How Data is Used
Data is used solely for whitelist management within Discord servers.
Wallet addresses are only stored for validation and verification purposes.
3. Data Sharing
User data is never sold or shared with third parties.
Server administrators may access collected data to manage whitelist submissions.
4. Data Retention & Removal
Wallet data and logs are stored as long as required for whitelist management.
Users may request removal of their submitted wallets by contacting a server administrator.
5. Security Measures
Reasonable measures are taken to protect stored data.
Users should not share sensitive personal information through the bot.
For any questions regarding these terms, contact the bot developer.
